# .nojekyll
# This empty file tells GitHub Pages NOT to process the site through Jekyll.
# Required because our folder names (shared/, admin/, etc.) and JS module
# imports would otherwise be mangled by Jekyll's build process.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   This file must exist at the ROOT of your GitHub Pages branch (gh-pages or main).
#   It has no content - its mere presence disables Jekyll processing.
